columns.name: Record Type
columns.description: Record  Type

columns.name: Borough
columns.description: Borough where property is located

columns.name: Easement
columns.description: E = Primary standard easement on the property F thru M = more than one easements are  placed on the property A = Air Rights B = Non Air Rights N = Non Transit P = Piers R = Railroads S = Street  U = U.S. Government

columns.name: Account Type
columns.description: Numeric code to indicate the type of charge 270 - 280 indicate Real Estate Charges

columns.name: Id Account
columns.description: Unique identification for selected accounts E.g. Meter # for water charges

columns.name: Date Account Period Begins
columns.description: Beginning data of tax period for the charge

columns.name: Date Account Period Ends
columns.description: Ending date of tax period for the charge

columns.name: Tax Class
columns.description: Property classification type used to determine the tax rate for calculating taxes

columns.name: Building Class
columns.description: 1 = 1 - 3 Unit Residences 1A = 1-3 Story Condominiums 1B = Residential Vacant Land 1C = 1-3 Unit Condominium (originally Tax Class 1) 1D = Select Bungalow Colonies2  = Apartments2A = Apartments with 4 - 6 Units 2B = Apartments with 7 - 10 Units 2C = Coops/Condos with 2 -10 Units 3 = Utilities (Except Ceiling Rail Roads) 4A = Utilities - Ceiling Rail Roads 4 = All Others

columns.name: Status
columns.description: C = Period has a credit Balance  D = Period has a debit balance O = period has zero balance

columns.name: Transaction Records Counter
columns.description: The number of transaction records that exist for this period

columns.name: Id Internal
columns.description: Borough, block, lot, easement formatted as one number Position 1 = Borough Position 2 - 6  = Block  Position 7 -10 = Lot Position 11 - 13 = Easement  Standard Easements  E = 140  F = 150   G = 160  H = 170  I = 180   J = 190 K = 200  L = 000, M = 000 A = 000 (Air Rights) B = 000 (Non Air Rights)  N = 230 (Non Transit)  P = 250 (Piers) R = 000 (Railroads) S = 000 (Street)  U = 000 (U.S. Government) Blank = 360 (No easement)

columns.name: Date Grace Period End
columns.description: Date after which a payment is considered late. Interest will be charged after this date.

columns.name: Amount Liability
columns.description: Total liability for this period

columns.name: Amount Collections
columns.description: Total collections for the period

columns.name: Amount Initial Total
columns.description: Total interest posted for this period. Interest is posted when the quarterly Statement of Account is generated or when a payment is made. The Date PI Thru Post field will give the interest calculated through date

columns.name: Amount Discount Early Pay
columns.description: Discount applied due to early payment

columns.name: Amount Balance
columns.description: Current balance due If zero, the period is fully paid  if positive, there is an outstanding liability for the period if negative, there is a credit balance for the period

columns.name: Date Update
columns.description: Date of the last transaction for this period (equals to the process date of the last transaction)

columns.name: Date Due Period
columns.description: Current due date for this period

columns.name: Date Penalty and Interest Thru Post
columns.description: Interest has been forecasted through this date

view.description:
Property tax balance and payment information for all active properties by period.

This dataset will remain as a historical record. More current and more detailed data can now be found here: https://data.cityofnewyork.us/City-Government/DOF-Property-Charges-Balance/scjx-j6np
